WEBVTT

00:06.000 --> 00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:31.652 --> 00:34.820
[ Machine whirs, click ]

00:34.822 --> 00:38.522
Girl: ♪ O beautiful ♪

00:38.622 --> 00:42.541
♪ for spacious skies ♪

00:42.543 --> 00:48.046
♪ for amber waves of grain ♪

00:48.048 --> 00:50.349
[ Faint explosions ]

00:50.351 --> 00:58.223
♪ For purple mountain majesty ♪

00:58.225 --> 01:04.446
♪ above the fruited plain ♪

01:04.447 --> 01:06.114
<i>Matt: Our final fight</i>
<i>with the Espheni</i>

01:06.116 --> 01:07.733
<i>didn't go as planned.</i>

01:07.735 --> 01:09.234
<i>But one thing was clear --</i>

01:09.236 --> 01:11.203
<i>this would be</i>
<i>the bloodiest battle yet.</i>

01:11.205 --> 01:12.571
Man: Incoming!

01:12.573 --> 01:19.127
Woman:
♪ God shed his grace on thee ♪

01:19.129 --> 01:23.215
♪ and crown thy good ♪

01:23.217 --> 01:26.668
♪ with brotherhood ♪

01:26.670 --> 01:33.392
♪ from sea to shining ♪

01:33.394 --> 01:35.143
♪ sea ♪

01:35.145 --> 01:39.145
<font color=#00FF00>♪ Falling Skies 5x10 ♪</font>
<font color=#00FFFF>Reborn</font>
Original Air Date on August 30, 2015

01:39.169 --> 01:43.369
== sync, corrected by <font color=#00FF00>elderman</font> ==
<font color=#00FFFF>@elder_man</font>

01:43.437 --> 01:46.188
[ Explosions ]

01:46.190 --> 01:47.823
[ Gasps ]

01:47.825 --> 01:51.109
Anne: They're circling
back around.

01:51.111 --> 01:52.661
That Espheni hub

01:52.663 --> 01:54.863
shone a goddamn spotlight
on this base!

01:54.865 --> 01:56.782
They're dropping
man-made bombs!

01:56.784 --> 01:59.117
Mark 82s from those
aircraft carriers.

01:59.119 --> 02:01.787
Bastards are using
our own weapons against us.

02:01.789 --> 02:04.706
[ Explosions ]
Here they come!

02:04.708 --> 02:09.377
[ Machine gunfire ]

02:09.380 --> 02:11.129
Aah!

02:15.636 --> 02:18.937
Maggie: They're retreating!
Keep firing!

02:20.557 --> 02:24.192
Take that,
you sons of bitches!

02:24.194 --> 02:26.528
[ Yells ]

02:26.530 --> 02:28.146
[ Screeches ]

02:28.148 --> 02:29.781
Whoa, Marty!

02:29.783 --> 02:32.951
[ Gunfire, screeching ]

02:32.953 --> 02:35.370
Marty. Hey, hey.

02:35.372 --> 02:36.655
Damn it.

02:36.657 --> 02:38.824
Don't you -- don't you die
on me.

02:38.826 --> 02:40.375
After I saved your ass...

02:40.377 --> 02:43.045
[ Weakly ]
I can't hear them anymore.

02:43.047 --> 02:45.213
They're gone?
Yeah, they're gone.

02:45.215 --> 02:47.332
We scared 'em off, all of 'em.

02:47.334 --> 02:49.551
They're gone. We got 'em.

02:49.553 --> 02:51.003
[ Labored breathing ]

02:51.005 --> 02:54.256
We're a...F-force
to be reckoned with.

02:54.258 --> 02:55.841
Aren't we, Colonel?

02:55.843 --> 02:58.927
And we never could've done it
without you.

02:58.929 --> 03:03.348
You know that. I couldn't have
done it without...

03:03.350 --> 03:05.067
Marty?

03:10.107 --> 03:11.940
I'll remember you.

03:17.281 --> 03:19.164
I'll remember.

03:20.367 --> 03:23.535
[ Whispers ]
I'll remember.

03:23.537 --> 03:26.204
Anne: [ Whispers ]
I'm sorry, Dan.

03:29.209 --> 03:33.712
Where the hell is this backup
that we've been countin' on?

03:33.714 --> 03:36.214
We sent a radio signal
of Tom's speech

03:36.216 --> 03:38.050
as far and wide
as we possibly could.

03:38.052 --> 03:39.885
There's gotta be other militia
on their way here.

03:39.887 --> 03:42.387
They're probably en route
to D.C.

03:42.389 --> 03:43.889
It's where we need to be.

03:43.891 --> 03:45.974
If the convoy leaves now,

03:45.976 --> 03:47.693
we expose ourselves
to the hornets

03:47.695 --> 03:51.530
in the dark, on the road.

03:51.532 --> 03:54.066
We stay another night.

03:56.153 --> 03:57.953
We stay another night.

04:05.079 --> 04:08.714
Tom: Depending on
what happens tomorrow,

04:08.716 --> 04:11.750
this might be
our last campfire together.

04:13.554 --> 04:16.254
I don't wanna put anybody
on the spot,

04:16.255 --> 04:17.889
but...

04:17.891 --> 04:19.757
If somebody has anything
that they'd like to say,

04:19.760 --> 04:21.676
this might be
a pretty good time.

04:32.489 --> 04:34.606
All right, I'll go first.

04:40.531 --> 04:42.030
[ Sighs heavily ]

04:42.032 --> 04:45.450
We began the last leg
of this journey

04:45.452 --> 04:50.172
with me admonishing you
to find your warrior...

04:51.959 --> 04:54.042
As I felt I'd found mine.

04:55.763 --> 04:59.598
To some of you, that may have
been just the boost you needed.

05:01.969 --> 05:05.720
And to others, I know
it didn't sit very well.

05:05.722 --> 05:08.640
And I understand that.

05:08.642 --> 05:11.109
This has been
a punishing journey,

05:12.046 --> 05:14.279
not just because of those
who we've lost,

05:14.281 --> 05:15.981
but because of the parts
of ourselves

05:15.983 --> 05:18.700
that we've had to sacrifice
along the way.

05:21.538 --> 05:23.321
Our innocence.

05:24.741 --> 05:27.409
And our hope.

05:27.411 --> 05:30.328
Maybe even part of our souls.

05:33.250 --> 05:35.717
But if you ask me,
it's been worth it.

05:44.011 --> 05:46.311
<i>You</i> are why I fight.

05:49.183 --> 05:51.183
And I don't know who's gonna
cross the finish line,

05:51.185 --> 05:53.685
but I can promise you this --
it will be crossed.

05:55.656 --> 05:58.607
This war <i> will</i> be won,

05:58.609 --> 06:00.692
because of you.

06:05.199 --> 06:08.333
Anybody else has anything they'd
like to say about anything,

06:08.335 --> 06:10.202
floor is yours.

06:10.204 --> 06:13.205
I think you said it all,
partner.

06:25.853 --> 06:29.054
[ Murmuring ]

06:33.477 --> 06:35.193
[ Bottles clink ]

06:35.195 --> 06:39.114
♪

06:46.623 --> 06:49.991
[ Engines roaring ]

06:53.297 --> 06:54.796
[ Blows air ]

07:05.759 --> 07:09.177
[ Man shouts indistinctly,
engines idling ]

07:13.317 --> 07:17.903
We're headed to D.C.,
part of Mason's militias.

07:19.273 --> 07:21.022
Looks like you guys are
stocked up pretty good here.

07:21.024 --> 07:23.358
You mind if we tag along
with ya?

07:23.360 --> 07:26.528
[ Wind whistling ]

07:26.530 --> 07:27.946
Not at all.

07:27.948 --> 07:31.283
I'm Tom Mason
of the 2nd Massachusetts.

07:33.287 --> 07:35.120
You're kidding me.

07:36.757 --> 07:39.291
You're Tom Mason?
[ Chuckles ]

07:39.293 --> 07:41.843
Hell, I thought you guys would
be a lot further down the road.

07:41.845 --> 07:46.181
Yeah, we did, too.

07:46.183 --> 07:47.382
Huh.

07:47.384 --> 07:50.969
Enos Ellis, 4th Maine.
[ Chuckles ]

07:50.971 --> 07:52.554
This is my crew.

07:52.556 --> 07:54.522
Got a few leftovers
from the 7th Connecticut.

07:54.524 --> 07:57.142
This here is Jickjack from the Ozarks.
[ Snorts ]

07:57.144 --> 07:59.361
And this over here
is Mothball from the Bronx.

07:59.363 --> 08:01.029
Meetcha.

08:02.449 --> 08:04.282
[ Clears throat ]

08:07.321 --> 08:09.821
Well, if you're Tom Mason,
this is your charter

08:09.823 --> 08:11.539
and we're your backup,
brother.

08:16.413 --> 08:19.998
I say we move out now,
while we got a window.

08:20.000 --> 08:23.802
Tom, one of our militia leaders
is on the radio.

08:23.804 --> 08:25.553
He needs to talk to you
right away.

08:26.807 --> 08:28.340
[ Static crackling ]

08:28.342 --> 08:30.008
Man: [ Over radio ] Our group
established a position

08:30.010 --> 08:31.343
outside the border.

08:31.345 --> 08:32.894
There's a wall,
for as far as we can see,

08:32.895 --> 08:34.679
around the whole D.C. mall.
Over.

08:34.681 --> 08:36.648
What kind of wall? Over.

08:36.650 --> 08:39.183
Man-made junk,
and it's covered in slime.

08:39.186 --> 08:41.986
It's about, like, 20 feet high
with these...

08:41.989 --> 08:44.689
these things,
these telescoping arms. Over.

08:44.691 --> 08:46.858
Skitterized humans.

08:46.860 --> 08:48.743
[ Static crackles ]
Stand by.

08:48.745 --> 08:49.944
[ Receiver thuds ]

08:49.946 --> 08:51.196
Hal: Well, we could go over it

08:51.198 --> 08:53.081
or we could try to find
a weak spot

08:53.083 --> 08:55.450
and cut right through it.
[ Indistinct conversations ]

08:55.452 --> 08:58.336
What about underground access?
Well, you got the subway tunnels.

08:58.338 --> 08:59.788
Obvious traps.

08:59.790 --> 09:03.041
What about the service tunnels?
They built them ages ago

09:03.043 --> 09:04.542
so politicians could cross
this mall

09:04.544 --> 09:06.261
without having to deal
with riffraff.

09:06.263 --> 09:08.463
I remember 'em well.
Born and raised here, sir.

09:08.465 --> 09:09.964
You're from D.C.?

09:09.966 --> 09:11.516
Can you map out
these tunnels?

09:11.518 --> 09:13.268
Tom Mason!

09:13.270 --> 09:15.220
You want us to be part
of this fight,

09:15.222 --> 09:16.805
you're gonna have to let us in
on the whole game plan.

09:16.807 --> 09:19.057
Listen, if we get cut to ribbons
trying to breach this wall,

09:19.059 --> 09:20.525
there's not gonna be much
of a fight.

09:20.527 --> 09:22.560
The man's working on it.
Give us a second.

09:22.562 --> 09:24.562
[ Snorts and sniffs ]

09:24.564 --> 09:26.064
[ Sighs ]

09:26.066 --> 09:29.784
Look, the Espheni are protecting
something big right here.

09:29.786 --> 09:30.707
Lincoln Memorial.

09:30.731 --> 09:32.404
We know they have
a hive-like culture.

09:32.406 --> 09:34.205
They all answer to
a queen bee creature.

09:34.207 --> 09:35.540
She has an organic connection

09:35.542 --> 09:36.958
with all Espheni forces
on earth.

09:36.960 --> 09:38.326
"Organic connection"?

09:38.328 --> 09:40.545
Forget this Jickjack.

09:40.547 --> 09:42.464
[ Sighs ]

09:42.466 --> 09:44.499
Lincoln Memorial. This is
where we think she's hiding.

09:44.501 --> 09:47.252
And our plan was to storm it
with overwhelming numbers,

09:47.254 --> 09:48.970
but that was before this wall.

09:48.972 --> 09:50.839
So we do a surgical strike
instead.

09:50.841 --> 09:52.140
We need
to take out the queen,

09:52.142 --> 09:54.092
and the Espheni forces
will fall.

09:54.094 --> 09:55.927
If my calculations
are correct,

09:55.929 --> 09:57.929
that should occur
almost instantly.

09:57.931 --> 10:00.432
Enos: What about you,

10:00.434 --> 10:04.352
alien who's here for reasons
I still don't understand?

10:04.354 --> 10:06.771
Can't we just carpet bomb
these bastards...

10:06.773 --> 10:08.606
from your spaceship?

10:10.110 --> 10:13.078
I'm afraid
that is not possible.

10:13.080 --> 10:16.581
However, Tom Mason has found
another way.

10:16.583 --> 10:20.618
My friend and I developed
what I guess you can call...

10:20.620 --> 10:23.121
A biological weapon.

10:23.123 --> 10:26.091
[ Squishing sound ]

10:28.462 --> 10:31.546
[ Scoffs ] Gimme a break.
What the hell's that gonna do?

10:31.548 --> 10:33.765
Ben: It's like
a network computer virus.

10:33.767 --> 10:35.884
You infect the host computer,
you infect them all.

10:35.886 --> 10:37.519
It works. We've tried it.

10:37.521 --> 10:40.555
And it's safe...
on humans, at least.

10:40.557 --> 10:42.440
This will kill the queen,

10:42.442 --> 10:44.692
and everything goes down
with the queen.

10:48.148 --> 10:49.614
[ Enos huffs ]

10:51.618 --> 10:54.486
You know, I was in Saigon
when the Tet offensive hit.

10:55.822 --> 10:57.622
Yeah, I thought Satan himself

10:57.624 --> 11:03.044
personally tried to burn
the goddamn place down.

11:05.081 --> 11:06.581
Only one of my company

11:06.583 --> 11:09.134
to crawl out of that
meat grinder alive was me.

11:09.136 --> 11:11.169
[ Chuckles ]

11:11.171 --> 11:13.838
This is nothing.

11:13.840 --> 11:15.390
We'll do it.

11:15.392 --> 11:18.927
These are the service tunnels,
here, here, and here.

11:18.929 --> 11:21.646
All right, I hope you have
a good memory, Lieutenant.

11:21.648 --> 11:24.015
Anthony.

11:24.017 --> 11:25.817
Think you can hold the fort,
solider?

11:25.819 --> 11:27.318
Yes, sir, Colonel.

11:27.320 --> 11:29.404
I need somebody to hold
this position.

11:29.406 --> 11:32.190
You and a team I select
will defend this base

11:32.192 --> 11:33.525
from the next attacking wave.

11:33.527 --> 11:35.493
But with all due respect,
Colonel,

11:35.495 --> 11:38.329
I'm here to fight,
not babysit.

11:38.331 --> 11:42.033
You could use me this last push
if you would just trust me.

11:42.035 --> 11:46.037
This <i> is</i> me trusting you.

11:46.039 --> 11:47.789
And this is
your last shot.

11:47.791 --> 11:49.958
You're gonna have to do it
with a clipped wing.

11:49.960 --> 11:51.759
Don't make me regret it.

11:51.761 --> 11:53.878
I'll take it.

11:53.880 --> 11:56.014
You made me whole again,
sir.

11:56.016 --> 11:58.349
Assembly in the mess hall.

11:58.351 --> 12:01.386
[ Clears throat ] Mr. Ellis.
If you wanna do this,

12:01.388 --> 12:03.471
you and your team will
attack that wall

12:03.473 --> 12:05.890
with every bit of artillery
you can carry.

12:05.892 --> 12:07.559
Make a distraction,

12:07.561 --> 12:09.394
get those forces away from
the Memorial.

12:09.396 --> 12:10.979
Meanwhile, our strike team
will go through

12:10.981 --> 12:12.447
this service tunnel right here...
[ Taps map ]

12:12.449 --> 12:13.948
Which should take us
right to Lincoln.

12:13.950 --> 12:16.618
So who was the unlucky one
to pull the short straw,

12:16.620 --> 12:19.621
gotta give this unholy bitch
her booster shot?

12:19.623 --> 12:21.239
Who do you think?

12:21.241 --> 12:23.208
Nice to finally meet

12:23.210 --> 12:25.460
another son of a bitch
who's as crazy as I am.

12:28.965 --> 12:31.216
♪

12:31.218 --> 12:33.134
Weaver: [ Over radio ]
2nd Mass on the move!

12:33.136 --> 12:36.337
Go, go, go!

12:36.339 --> 12:38.673
Man: Don't let them engage!

12:38.675 --> 12:40.174
Fire at will. Over.

12:40.176 --> 12:42.260
[ Rapid gunfire ]

12:42.262 --> 12:44.095
Man: We've reached
our destination.

12:44.097 --> 12:46.814
2nd Mass going radio silent.

12:46.816 --> 12:48.766
[ Door bangs open ]

12:57.911 --> 13:00.328
Hal: No Espheni guards.
Ben: Don't jinx it.

13:01.448 --> 13:04.666
Weaver: [ Whispers ] Okay,
that should be it.

13:09.873 --> 13:12.123
[ Whoosh ]

13:12.125 --> 13:14.125
[ Clank ]

13:18.265 --> 13:21.132
[ Screeching in distance ]

13:25.355 --> 13:27.972
Whoa. Lights off.

13:27.974 --> 13:29.807
[ Clicking ]

13:33.613 --> 13:35.813
[ High-pitched sound
in distance ]

13:40.487 --> 13:43.488
[ Slithering sound ]

13:48.995 --> 13:50.828
[ Whispering ] Easy.

13:50.830 --> 13:53.247
Easy.

13:53.249 --> 13:55.333
[ Low-pitched roar ]

13:58.505 --> 14:01.889
[ High-pitched sound
in distance continues ]

14:03.760 --> 14:07.312
[ Whooshing sound ]

14:11.434 --> 14:13.851
Anne:
[ Whispers ] What are they?

14:18.525 --> 14:22.276
[ Whispers ] Do not touch.

14:25.031 --> 14:26.698
[ High-pitched screech ]

14:29.295 --> 14:31.128
[ Purring sound ]

14:31.130 --> 14:32.829
[ Whooshing sound ]

14:34.416 --> 14:36.416
Weaver: Great.

14:36.418 --> 14:39.236
This had to be the road
to ground zero.

14:40.422 --> 14:43.840
I'm afraid it is not good.

14:47.192 --> 14:48.725
Elaborate.

14:48.727 --> 14:51.361
Baby Espheni.

14:51.363 --> 14:54.948
Cool temperatures
and an absence of sunlight

14:54.950 --> 14:57.233
provide a perfect
breeding ground.

14:57.235 --> 14:59.235
When they are hatched,

14:59.237 --> 15:02.238
Espheni overlords are
far more...

15:02.240 --> 15:04.874
violent than when fully grown.

15:04.876 --> 15:08.211
Wait. So they're more violent
when they're babies?

15:08.213 --> 15:11.831
My broodmates disturbed
a nest once.

15:11.833 --> 15:15.251
The hatchlings tore through
all of them effortlessly.

15:15.253 --> 15:18.805
11 dead in seconds.

15:21.259 --> 15:24.010
It is best
we don't disturb them.

15:24.012 --> 15:26.646
That's an important
safety tip.

15:26.648 --> 15:28.148
[ Static crackles ]
[ Man speaks indistinctly over radio ]

15:28.150 --> 15:29.599
Shh! Shh! Shh!
[ Volume turns down ]

15:29.601 --> 15:32.902
[ Warbling and groaning sound ]

15:32.904 --> 15:36.489
[ Whooshing continues ]

15:36.491 --> 15:40.109
[ Whispers ] We're gonna
keep going. Lights on.

15:40.111 --> 15:41.778
[ Click ]
Move.

15:41.780 --> 15:44.614
[ Clicking ]

15:46.368 --> 15:50.203
[ Panting ]
We should turn back.

15:50.205 --> 15:52.622
We should find another way
into the city,

15:52.624 --> 15:54.958
even if it takes longer.
What's wrong?

15:54.960 --> 15:57.293
[ Voice breaks ]
Something about these eggs.

15:57.295 --> 15:59.262
[ Inhales deeply ]
The embryo.

15:59.264 --> 16:02.715
The unborn child.

16:02.717 --> 16:04.133
What?

16:04.135 --> 16:05.802
You know I just had to watch

16:05.804 --> 16:08.104
some freaky carbon copy
of my own flesh and blood

16:08.106 --> 16:09.522
come back to life.

16:09.524 --> 16:11.858
And I didn't just
have to see her,

16:11.860 --> 16:14.110
but watch her be killed --
my own daughter.

16:14.112 --> 16:16.068
That wasn't Lexi.
You know that wasn't Lexi.

16:16.091 --> 16:17.031
I know.

16:17.032 --> 16:19.315
What?

16:20.869 --> 16:23.236
What is it? Tell me.

16:25.040 --> 16:27.457
I'm pregnant.

16:29.160 --> 16:30.710
You serious?

16:38.670 --> 16:39.752
[ Sniffles ]

16:39.754 --> 16:41.504
We're gonna be okay.
[ Inhales sharply ]

16:41.506 --> 16:43.756
We're gonna get
through this.

16:43.758 --> 16:47.760
[ Exhales sharply,
sniffles ]

16:47.762 --> 16:49.479
[ High-pitched sounds
in distance ]

16:49.481 --> 16:51.814
Keep following
this east tunnel.

16:51.816 --> 16:55.351
Should be a stairwell up here
in a couple of seconds.

16:56.688 --> 16:58.521
Yeah.

16:58.523 --> 17:00.990
I mean, I'm <i> almost</i> sure

17:00.992 --> 17:03.026
that'll take us to
the access point on the mall

17:03.028 --> 17:04.861
closest to Lincoln.

17:04.863 --> 17:09.165
Nothing like hanging the fate
of humanity on "almost," but...

17:09.166 --> 17:12.502
We used to use these tunnels
as kids.

17:12.503 --> 17:15.872
Drink beer, chase girls.

17:15.874 --> 17:18.290
City was <i> alive</i> then.

17:18.292 --> 17:22.295
I thought you said
these tunnels were fortified

17:22.297 --> 17:24.881
by the Secret Service
for D.C. big shots.

17:24.883 --> 17:26.933
And their kids.

17:28.553 --> 17:30.219
Who was the big shot?

17:30.221 --> 17:32.555
My mom.

17:32.557 --> 17:34.307
She was always talking about

17:34.309 --> 17:37.560
the importance of service
and sacrifice.

17:37.562 --> 17:40.113
I wish I got the chance to show her.
[ Groans ]

17:40.115 --> 17:45.318
Like Martin,
back at the base.

17:45.320 --> 17:47.320
He died a soldier.

17:48.623 --> 17:50.239
A hero.

17:51.910 --> 17:56.045
Here we are. Here we are.
This is it.

17:56.047 --> 17:57.914
No.

17:57.916 --> 18:00.550
Lieutenant Marty died
for one reason

18:00.552 --> 18:02.585
and one reason only --

18:02.587 --> 18:06.506
that hornet got him before
he could shoot it, period.

18:06.508 --> 18:09.592
Dying didn't make him anything
he wasn't already.

18:11.262 --> 18:13.396
We owe him a lot,

18:13.398 --> 18:16.099
but there's no heroism
in being a martyr.

18:16.101 --> 18:19.736
Getting yourself killed is not
something you wanna do.

18:19.738 --> 18:22.488
That'd just be stupid,
wouldn't it?

18:26.194 --> 18:28.861
Yes, sir.

18:28.863 --> 18:30.413
Let's go.

18:39.090 --> 18:41.958
[ Low rumbling ]

18:43.545 --> 18:46.879
[ Whooshing,
high-pitched sound in distance ]

19:05.233 --> 19:07.367
I've never been so terrified.

19:07.369 --> 19:08.701
You're gonna feel a lot better

19:08.703 --> 19:10.953
once we bomb the shit out of
this place.

19:10.955 --> 19:14.457
Well, let's just hope that
we replace it with something --

19:14.459 --> 19:15.992
better. [ Chuckles ]

19:15.994 --> 19:17.326
Yeah.
I know.

19:17.328 --> 19:18.961
You know, sooner or later,

19:18.963 --> 19:21.581
you gotta make up
your mind, right?

19:21.583 --> 19:24.333
I made up my mind
a long time ago.

19:24.335 --> 19:25.835
Thank you, Dr. Phil.

19:25.837 --> 19:28.588
Let's just hope
the lucky winner agrees.

19:28.590 --> 19:31.974
[ Whooshing,
high-pitched sound in distance ]

19:39.684 --> 19:41.684
[ Whispers ] Hey!
Don't touch that.

19:41.686 --> 19:44.187
Yeah, I know. Not an idiot.

19:44.189 --> 19:48.357
I just wanna see what, uh, one
of these buggers looks like.

19:52.864 --> 19:54.080
[ Whispers ] Matt!

19:54.082 --> 19:59.001
[ Squishing ]

19:59.003 --> 20:01.838
[ Gasps ]

20:04.008 --> 20:05.708
[ Hisses ]

20:05.710 --> 20:08.377
[ Screeches ]
[ Grunts ]

20:08.379 --> 20:12.215
Stay down.
Aah!

20:12.217 --> 20:15.101
[ Shouting indistinctly ]

20:15.103 --> 20:16.602
Cease fire!

20:16.604 --> 20:18.688
Cease fire!
[ Gunfire stops ]

20:24.813 --> 20:28.064
[ Whispers ]
What's going on now?

20:29.400 --> 20:32.535
[ Squishing continues ]

20:36.207 --> 20:37.490
I'll take point.
Yeah.

20:37.492 --> 20:38.991
Shh! Shh, shh, shh.

20:38.993 --> 20:40.877
What is that?

20:40.879 --> 20:42.879
[ Creaking ]

20:47.218 --> 20:48.751
[ Whispers ] Hey, I'm gonna...
Shh. Shh, shh, shh, shh.

20:48.753 --> 20:50.636
[ Slithering and creaking
continues ]

20:50.638 --> 20:53.172
What's that sound?

20:53.174 --> 20:55.558
Easy.

21:15.830 --> 21:20.616
[ Creaking,
shrieking in distance ]

21:20.618 --> 21:22.869
[ Shriek fades ]

21:26.424 --> 21:28.925
Shh, shh, shh, shh.

21:28.927 --> 21:31.677
[ Crunch ]
[ Screeching ]

21:31.679 --> 21:33.129
Oh, I got it!

21:33.131 --> 21:36.132
[ Bullets ricocheting ]
[ Shrieking ]

21:38.636 --> 21:40.553
Reload!
I'm out! Loading grenade!

21:40.555 --> 21:41.771
Get back!

21:41.773 --> 21:44.106
Everybody, get down!
Get down!

21:46.277 --> 21:48.361
Tom!

21:48.363 --> 21:49.645
Will you marry me?

21:49.647 --> 21:51.197
[ Gasps ] What?

21:51.199 --> 21:52.648
Tom!
Get down!

21:52.650 --> 21:54.817
I gotta know. Will you?
[ Click ]

21:54.819 --> 21:57.453
Come and get it,
you sons of bitches!

21:57.455 --> 21:59.989
Wolf, don't!
Everybody, take cover!

21:59.991 --> 22:01.207
Yes.

22:01.209 --> 22:04.210
[ Grenade whistles,
explosion, shrieking ]

22:04.212 --> 22:06.128
Aah!

22:09.075 --> 22:11.993
[ rumbling ]

22:13.914 --> 22:16.281
Hal: [ Muffled ] Dad?!

22:16.283 --> 22:19.117
<i>[ High-pitched whine ]</i>

22:19.812 --> 22:23.730
[ Muffled ] Tom! Wolf!

22:23.733 --> 22:26.067
Anne: [ Muffled ] Tom?

22:26.068 --> 22:27.618
[ Coughs ]

22:27.620 --> 22:29.703
Weaver: Lieutenant?! Tom!

22:32.291 --> 22:34.958
Anne: Tom?
Tom!

22:34.960 --> 22:36.710
Tom?
Lieutenant?

22:41.417 --> 22:43.584
[ Gasping ]

22:47.339 --> 22:50.174
Matt: Dad?
Hal: Dad!

22:50.176 --> 22:52.893
Make a noise! Say something!

22:52.896 --> 22:54.979
Tom!

22:54.981 --> 22:57.098
[ Crumbling ]
Tom: [ Coughs ] Yeah?

22:57.100 --> 22:59.684
Tom?
Matt: [ Muffled ] Say something!

22:59.686 --> 23:03.021
Tom: [ Coughs ] I'm okay.

23:03.023 --> 23:05.440
Ohh. Thank God.

23:05.441 --> 23:06.690
[ Coughs ]

23:06.692 --> 23:08.325
I don't see Wolf.

23:08.327 --> 23:11.245
Is he on your side? Ah!

23:11.247 --> 23:14.615
Weaver: Yeah, he's on our side,
but he didn't make it.

23:14.617 --> 23:18.418
You took 'em all out, didn't ya,
2nd Lieutenant Demarcus Wolf?

23:18.420 --> 23:22.122
Well...You made your mom proud.

23:22.125 --> 23:24.209
Tom: Where's Anne?

23:24.210 --> 23:28.178
I'm right here.
Are you sure you're okay?

23:28.180 --> 23:29.796
Never better.

23:29.798 --> 23:31.882
[ High-pitched sound in distance ]
[ Grunts ]

23:31.884 --> 23:34.685
[ Whooshing ]

23:34.687 --> 23:36.720
[ Lowered voice ] Everybody keep
your voices down, though.

23:36.722 --> 23:38.722
Doesn't look like we can
get through to you from here.

23:38.724 --> 23:40.857
Hey, we're all right, Dad.
Don't worry about us.

23:40.859 --> 23:42.643
You keep going. We're gonna find
another way to get to you.

23:42.645 --> 23:45.062
We're gonna find another
tunnel to the mall.

23:45.064 --> 23:46.813
Let's get out of here.

23:46.815 --> 23:49.199
[ Sighs ]

23:49.201 --> 23:52.452
A-all right, stick together.

23:52.454 --> 23:55.072
Be careful.
[ Whooshing sounds ]

23:55.074 --> 23:57.658
Weaver: Yeah. You, too.

23:57.660 --> 23:59.660
Let's finish this job...

24:00.663 --> 24:03.080
For the ones who didn't
make it.

24:07.169 --> 24:08.585
Anne?

24:08.587 --> 24:10.887
What? Okay.

24:10.889 --> 24:12.306
[ Whispers ] Bye, baby.

24:14.310 --> 24:17.094
[ Panting ]
We'll find him.

24:22.401 --> 24:25.602
[ High-pitched sound
in distance ]

24:30.109 --> 24:31.658
[ Grunts ]

24:34.330 --> 24:37.581
[ Slithering,
high-pitched sound continues ]

24:45.624 --> 24:49.092
[ Slithering,
high-pitched sound continues ]

24:56.135 --> 24:59.386
[ Low-pitching beating sound ]

25:01.473 --> 25:05.475
[ Low roar in distance,
high-pitched sound continues ]

25:18.657 --> 25:23.043
[ Screeching ]

25:23.045 --> 25:26.496
[ Explosions in distance ]

25:33.256 --> 25:35.173
My God.

25:36.759 --> 25:39.176
They're moving in.

25:42.815 --> 25:45.682
♪

26:01.116 --> 26:02.699
[ Loud whoosh ]

26:05.037 --> 26:07.838
[ Screech ]

26:07.840 --> 26:09.873
[ Clatter ]

26:11.043 --> 26:14.544
[ Rumbling ]

26:16.131 --> 26:17.631
[ Roar ]

26:17.633 --> 26:19.850
[ Heavy running footsteps ]

26:21.103 --> 26:24.721
[ Squawking ]

26:24.723 --> 26:28.308
[ High-pitched sound
in distance ]

26:37.069 --> 26:40.203
[ Loud screech ]

26:52.418 --> 26:54.968
[ Low rumbling ]

27:02.344 --> 27:05.846
Female voice:
[ Echoing ] Smell the blood.

27:05.848 --> 27:07.814
Smell the blood.

27:17.276 --> 27:19.242
[ Growls ]

27:46.532 --> 27:48.857
Here we are.

27:48.858 --> 27:51.442
[ Whispers ] Anne?
Hey, you all right?

27:51.444 --> 27:53.394
Yeah, I'm fine.
I'm just a little tired.

27:53.396 --> 27:55.145
Almost there. We're going to find him.
Okay.

27:55.147 --> 27:57.364
We're going to get through.
Okay.

27:58.901 --> 28:00.651
[ Door bangs open ]

28:09.078 --> 28:11.745
[ Rattling sound ]

28:11.747 --> 28:14.081
[ Growls ]

28:14.083 --> 28:15.633
[ Slithering sound ]

28:18.387 --> 28:19.920
If you wanna talk to me,

28:19.922 --> 28:22.172
have the courage to look me
in the eye!

28:22.174 --> 28:25.593
[ Growls and roars ]

28:25.595 --> 28:27.428
Uhh!

28:27.430 --> 28:30.481
Aah! [ Grunting ]

28:33.069 --> 28:34.735
Is this close enough?

28:34.737 --> 28:37.271
[ Slithers ]

28:37.273 --> 28:38.856
[ High-pitched sound ]

28:38.858 --> 28:41.191
[ Distorted voice ] Do you even
know what your people did

28:41.193 --> 28:42.776
to deserve this fate?

28:42.778 --> 28:44.278
I don't care.

28:44.280 --> 28:49.416
Aw. Has intellectual curiosity
given way to your bloodlust?

28:49.418 --> 28:51.585
We didn't do anything!

28:51.587 --> 28:54.788
Please, allow me...

28:54.790 --> 28:56.256
to explain.

28:56.258 --> 28:58.425
[ Whispering ] To explain.

28:58.427 --> 29:00.210
To explain.
[ Beating sound ]

29:00.212 --> 29:01.845
[ Whoosh ]

29:01.847 --> 29:04.014
<i>Queen: The Espheni followed</i>
<i>our own prophecy.</i>

29:04.016 --> 29:06.050
<i>We expanded our empire</i>
<i>from planet to planet.</i>

29:06.052 --> 29:07.768
<i>[ Voice echoing ]</i>

29:07.770 --> 29:12.439
<i>But earth was unlike</i>
<i>anything encountered before.</i>

29:12.441 --> 29:15.309
<i>The only habitable planet</i>
<i>in this galaxy.</i>

29:15.311 --> 29:18.312
<i>Immeasurable strategic value.</i>

29:18.314 --> 29:21.281
<i>1,500 of</i> your <i> years ago,</i>

29:21.283 --> 29:24.151
<i>it was inhabited</i>
<i>by primitives.</i>

29:24.153 --> 29:28.155
<i>I sent my fiercest warrior</i>
<i>to lead the invasion --</i>

29:28.157 --> 29:30.658
<i>my prized daughter.</i>

29:30.660 --> 29:33.994
<i>But you were far stronger</i>
<i>than we ever imagined.</i>

29:33.996 --> 29:35.663
<i>You slaughtered her.</i>

29:35.665 --> 29:37.297
<i>[ Voice doubling ]</i>
<i>I vowed to return</i>

29:37.299 --> 29:39.667
<i>a thousand times stronger</i>
<i>to avenge her death...</i>

29:39.669 --> 29:43.053
<i>And wipe out humanity.</i>

29:44.890 --> 29:46.640
[ Huffs ]

29:46.642 --> 29:49.727
[ Stomping,
shrieking in distance ]

29:49.729 --> 29:52.846
Well, what did you expect?!
[ Stomping continues ]

29:52.848 --> 29:54.264
You provoked us!

29:54.266 --> 29:57.901
[ Distorted voice ]
Those savages consumed the flesh

29:57.903 --> 30:00.654
of my daughter
to gain her strength,

30:00.656 --> 30:04.024
so I am going
to consume <i> you.</i>

30:04.026 --> 30:07.444
I will leave your head
for the spike.

30:07.446 --> 30:09.913
[ High-pitched rattling ]

30:09.915 --> 30:14.535
The snake of human rebellion
will be without its head,

30:14.537 --> 30:17.705
and the rest will go,
as you say,

30:17.707 --> 30:19.757
like lambs to the slaughter.
[ Slithering sound ]

30:19.759 --> 30:22.960
You still don't get it,
do you?

30:22.962 --> 30:24.595
You can kill me.

30:24.597 --> 30:26.547
You can put my head
on a stick.

30:26.549 --> 30:29.600
You failed to learn the lesson
for the second time!

30:29.602 --> 30:31.685
We will never surrender!

30:32.888 --> 30:35.439
♪

30:46.986 --> 30:49.620
I think we're a lot
further south than we'd hoped.

30:49.622 --> 30:51.071
We'll get to him.

30:51.073 --> 30:53.290
We can take point.
Weaver: Good. Good.

30:53.292 --> 30:55.409
Think you can keep up with me,
even without spikes?

30:55.411 --> 30:56.744
I'll kick your ass.

30:56.746 --> 30:59.246
Weaver: Watch your 6s.
Watch your 6s.

30:59.248 --> 31:01.298
Let's go.

31:01.300 --> 31:04.084
Let's go. Come on.

31:07.339 --> 31:09.256
Here we are.

31:09.258 --> 31:11.475
Good, good.

31:11.477 --> 31:12.926
[ Anne groans ]

31:12.928 --> 31:14.595
Anne.

31:14.597 --> 31:16.480
No, no. No, no.
What's wrong?

31:16.482 --> 31:18.182
No, no, don't stop for me.

31:18.184 --> 31:20.017
[ Whispers ] I just need
to catch my breath.

31:20.019 --> 31:21.268
[ Echoes ] Oh!

31:21.270 --> 31:24.071
<i>[ High-pitched ringing,</i>
<i>rapid heartbeat ]</i>

31:24.073 --> 31:26.857
[ Muffled ] Anne!

31:28.194 --> 31:30.110
[ Groans ]
What is it?

31:30.112 --> 31:31.612
Uhh! [ Gasping ]

31:31.614 --> 31:34.031
What's wrong? What happened?
[ Panting ]

31:34.033 --> 31:36.784
What's the matter with you?
Huh?

31:36.786 --> 31:38.168
[ Whispering ] S-s--
I'm sorry. [ Panting ]

31:38.170 --> 31:42.122
Whoa. Hey, uh, somebody get
a medic bag over --

31:42.124 --> 31:43.791
I'm sorry.
Over --

31:43.793 --> 31:45.509
I think I got hit
by shrapnel.

31:45.511 --> 31:46.927
You got hit by shrapnel?

31:46.929 --> 31:48.796
You -- you got nothing
to be sorry about.

31:48.798 --> 31:52.216
[ Whimpering ]
Just...

31:52.218 --> 31:54.635
Y-you're gonna be fine.

31:54.637 --> 31:56.520
We're almost there.

31:56.522 --> 31:59.556
I -- hey, I'm not gonna
leave without you. Hey.

31:59.558 --> 32:00.774
I'm sorry.

32:00.776 --> 32:02.559
You -- you're all right.

32:02.561 --> 32:04.278
[ Wheezing ]
[ Unzips bag ]

32:04.280 --> 32:06.814
You're --
hey. Hey, friend.

32:06.816 --> 32:09.566
[ Voice echoing ] Hey, friend.
We're almost there.

32:09.568 --> 32:11.401
We got you.

32:11.403 --> 32:13.620
[ Whimpering ]

32:13.622 --> 32:17.157
♪

32:17.159 --> 32:20.494
[ Gasping, wheezing ]

32:20.496 --> 32:25.249
[ Weaver whispering
indistinctly ]

32:25.251 --> 32:29.336
♪

32:29.338 --> 32:31.221
Don't you go.

32:31.223 --> 32:33.090
We can't go on
without you.

32:38.639 --> 32:41.206
♪

32:41.207 --> 32:43.541
[ Grunting ]

32:43.544 --> 32:46.211
Come on. Come on.

32:46.212 --> 32:48.262
[ Grunting ]

32:48.265 --> 32:52.301
[ Stomping, slithering sound ]
Come on!

32:52.303 --> 32:54.052
[ Rapid stomping ]

32:56.774 --> 32:58.774
[ Distorted voice ]
Smell the blood.

32:58.776 --> 33:00.726
Smell the blood.

33:00.727 --> 33:02.894
Smell the blood.

33:02.896 --> 33:04.445
Smell the blood.

33:04.447 --> 33:06.147
Smell the blood.

33:06.149 --> 33:10.234
Smell the blood! Smell
the blood! Smell the blood!

33:10.236 --> 33:14.038
[ Grunting ]

33:14.040 --> 33:17.575
[ Squish ]
Aah! Aah! Aah!

33:17.577 --> 33:20.912
[ Wheezing ]
Uhh! Uhh! Aah!

33:20.914 --> 33:23.130
[ Continues wheezing ]

33:23.132 --> 33:27.218
[ Slithering and whooshing ]

33:43.436 --> 33:47.271
[ Wheezing continues ]

33:47.273 --> 33:48.940
[ Squish ]

33:48.942 --> 33:53.611
[ Roaring ]

33:53.613 --> 33:56.080
[ Screams ]

33:56.082 --> 33:59.116
[ Explosion, scream stops ]

33:59.118 --> 34:02.453
[ Gasps ]
[ Debris falling ]

34:09.295 --> 34:11.795
[ Screams ]

34:11.797 --> 34:15.800
[ Panting ]

34:24.643 --> 34:27.812
[ Explosions in distance ]

34:47.467 --> 34:48.799
[ Gasping ]

34:48.801 --> 34:51.585
[ Whispers ] I'm not gonna go
without you, Anne. Okay?

34:51.588 --> 34:53.170
You can't go.

34:53.172 --> 34:55.590
No.
[ Gasps and inhales sharply ]

34:55.592 --> 34:58.342
We got it. You're okay.

34:58.344 --> 35:00.728
[ Gasping rapidly ]
Don't you go.

35:00.730 --> 35:02.346
Not you.

35:02.348 --> 35:05.232
Don't go.

35:05.234 --> 35:07.852
Don't go.

35:14.777 --> 35:17.778
[ Gasps ]

35:17.780 --> 35:19.363
My friend.

35:28.591 --> 35:32.760
Hey. Hey.

35:32.762 --> 35:35.212
[ Sniffles ]

35:45.391 --> 35:48.275
[ Explosions ]

35:48.277 --> 35:50.394
Dad!
[ Rapid footsteps approach ]

35:50.396 --> 35:52.446
Ben?

35:52.448 --> 35:56.951
♪

36:00.407 --> 36:02.373
Did it work?

36:02.970 --> 36:06.243
They're all dead.

36:06.245 --> 36:08.996
Every last one of them.

36:20.727 --> 36:23.310
What is it?

36:37.527 --> 36:39.777
Hey.

36:39.779 --> 36:42.580
[ Inhales sharply ] Anne...

36:53.176 --> 36:55.459
[ Breathing unevenly ]

36:55.461 --> 36:59.630
[ Sniffling ]

37:05.054 --> 37:09.223
[ Crying ]

37:15.114 --> 37:18.816
<i>[ Heartbeat thumping ]</i>

37:18.818 --> 37:21.035
<i>[ Voice echoing ]</i>
<i>You are safe and sound.</i>

37:21.037 --> 37:23.704
<i>We come in peace.</i>

37:23.706 --> 37:27.658
<i>[ Heartbeat thumping ]</i>

37:29.295 --> 37:32.580
[ High-pitched ringing ]

37:34.000 --> 37:35.299
Move back.

37:35.301 --> 37:38.052
I have to do this alone.

37:38.054 --> 37:40.387
[ Grunts ]

38:14.457 --> 38:17.041
I did everything you asked!

38:18.594 --> 38:20.928
I believed in you!

38:20.930 --> 38:22.713
I delivered you vengeance!

38:26.102 --> 38:29.103
You saved me
so I could help you!

38:31.190 --> 38:33.557
Now you're gonna save her!

38:35.611 --> 38:37.194
Help her!

38:39.899 --> 38:41.699
Help her!

38:46.956 --> 38:48.739
[ Voice breaks ] Help her!

38:55.832 --> 38:58.582
♪

39:31.250 --> 39:33.617
Well, well, well.

39:37.006 --> 39:39.423
[ Grunts ]

39:42.628 --> 39:46.547
The decent folks
with the Tennessee,

39:46.549 --> 39:49.633
they took me in.

39:49.635 --> 39:52.136
Some humanity.

39:53.473 --> 39:57.442
Imagine that, Tom.
[ Grunts ]

39:57.443 --> 39:59.894
[ Groans ]
In this day and age.

39:59.896 --> 40:03.230
[ Grunts ]

40:03.232 --> 40:05.482
Taking mercy
on the likes of me.

40:07.653 --> 40:09.453
Uhh! Ah!

40:14.410 --> 40:17.711
She's gone, isn't she?

40:17.713 --> 40:19.713
[ Grunting ]

40:24.003 --> 40:25.753
You know...

40:27.556 --> 40:29.807
All this time,

40:29.809 --> 40:34.345
I thought it would
give me satisfaction...

40:34.347 --> 40:36.513
that your suffering...

40:38.150 --> 40:40.567
would make me feel better.

40:46.943 --> 40:48.692
[ Clicks hammer ]

41:11.851 --> 41:13.684
Seems only fitting.

41:15.187 --> 41:16.720
Besides...

41:18.524 --> 41:21.809
I had the jump on you.

41:30.236 --> 41:33.203
[ Wheezes ]

41:33.205 --> 41:34.822
The war is over.

41:34.824 --> 41:37.741
I'm done killing.

41:37.743 --> 41:40.794
[ Continues wheezing ]

41:48.637 --> 41:50.921
You're a pain in the ass,
Mason.

41:50.923 --> 41:54.258
[ Wheezes ]

41:54.260 --> 41:58.479
[ Exhales slowly ]

41:58.481 --> 42:02.433
[ Waves crashing ]

42:15.233 --> 42:17.066
[ Whirring ]

42:17.068 --> 42:18.401
[ Click ]

42:18.403 --> 42:22.471
<i>Woman: ♪ America ♪</i>

42:22.473 --> 42:24.707
<i>♪ America ♪</i>

42:24.710 --> 42:26.510
<i>Matt: And as</i>
<i>the world's survivors emerged</i>

42:26.511 --> 42:28.277
<i>from the smoldering aftermath,</i>

42:28.279 --> 42:29.845
<i>we found that we reached</i>
<i>for each other,</i>

42:29.847 --> 42:35.217
<i>bonded together in ways</i>
<i>we never had before.</i>

42:35.219 --> 42:36.752
♪ And crown thy... ♪

42:36.754 --> 42:38.387
<i>Matt: We need a leader,</i>
<i>of course,</i>

42:38.389 --> 42:41.807
<i>which is why</i>
<i>we're gathered here today.</i>

42:41.810 --> 42:43.760
<i>Matt and Tom: But that need is</i>
<i>now truly informed</i>

42:43.761 --> 42:45.644
<i>by the consent</i>
<i>of the governed,</i>

42:45.646 --> 42:48.180
<i>just like the Founding Fathers</i>
<i>of America intended.</i>

42:48.182 --> 42:49.849
♪ Shining ♪

42:49.852 --> 42:51.735
<i>Tom:</i>
<i>Differences, arguments,</i>

42:51.736 --> 42:54.653
<i>even impassioned debate --</i>
<i>these are all good things.</i>

42:54.655 --> 42:57.940
<i>But in the end,</i>
<i>we're all in this together.</i>

42:59.610 --> 43:03.279
[ Indistinct conversations ]

43:08.252 --> 43:09.952
This is excellent work.

43:09.954 --> 43:11.787
I'm very proud of you.

43:11.789 --> 43:14.290
You wanna be
Secretary of State?

43:14.292 --> 43:16.759
Not really.
I-I have a date.

43:16.761 --> 43:19.295
Okay.

43:19.297 --> 43:21.013
[ Sighs deeply ]
They're gonna love it.

43:21.015 --> 43:23.516
They might even ask you
to be president again.

43:23.518 --> 43:25.101
I've already said no twice.

43:25.103 --> 43:26.469
Well, you can say no
a third time,

43:26.471 --> 43:27.970
like George Washington.

43:27.972 --> 43:31.807
Just give a good speech.
You know, no pressure.

43:31.809 --> 43:33.142
No pressure.

43:33.144 --> 43:34.610
I'm just a teacher.

43:34.612 --> 43:36.812
Yeah, right.
Professor Emeritus

43:36.814 --> 43:39.482
at the new United Nations
University. [ Chuckles ]

43:39.484 --> 43:41.067
All the world leaders are
gonna be coming around,

43:41.069 --> 43:43.536
asking for advice
before they do a damn thing.

43:44.956 --> 43:47.323
Well...Still just a teacher.

43:47.325 --> 43:49.241
Watch your language.

43:49.243 --> 43:51.077
[ Taps book ]

43:51.080 --> 43:54.331
<i>Tom: Despite the horror,</i>
<i>the loss, the death,</i>

43:54.332 --> 43:56.298
<i>the war with the Espheni</i>
<i>might have ultimately made us</i>

43:56.300 --> 43:58.000
<i>better human beings.</i>

43:58.002 --> 44:02.505
[ Indistinct conversations
continue ]

44:02.507 --> 44:04.890
<i>We can actually christen</i>
<i>a new melting pot --</i>

44:04.892 --> 44:06.142
<i>a worldwide one.</i>

44:06.144 --> 44:08.144
<i>Our first goal --</i>
<i>to welcome those,</i>

44:08.146 --> 44:11.680
<i>especially those whose methods</i>
<i>we don't always understand.</i>

44:11.682 --> 44:14.683
[ Indistinct conversations
continue ]

44:14.685 --> 44:17.269
[ Speaks indistinctly ]

44:17.271 --> 44:21.073
<i>But our newfound openness,</i>
<i>our egalitarianism,</i>

44:21.075 --> 44:22.408
<i>should never come</i>

44:22.410 --> 44:24.193
<i>at the expense</i>
<i>of our vigilance.</i>

44:24.195 --> 44:26.579
[ Speaks indistinctly ]

44:26.581 --> 44:28.197
<i>For as the man said,</i>

44:28.199 --> 44:30.366
<i>"those who fail</i>
<i>to learn from history..."</i>

44:30.368 --> 44:31.667
Good luck.

44:31.669 --> 44:34.336
<i>"...are doomed to repeat it."</i>

44:34.338 --> 44:36.038
<i>And we will forevermore</i>

44:36.040 --> 44:38.040
<i>be keeping our eyes</i>
<i>on the skies.</i>

44:38.042 --> 44:39.708
♪

44:39.710 --> 44:42.428
<i>Now begins the work</i>
<i>of rebuilding our world.</i>

44:42.430 --> 44:43.712
Mm.

44:43.714 --> 44:45.297
<i>And in that work,</i>

44:45.299 --> 44:47.550
<i>we have both the responsibility</i>
<i>and an opportunity</i>

44:47.552 --> 44:49.185
<i>to apply those lessons.</i>

44:49.187 --> 44:52.805
<i>And if we do, we have a chance</i>
<i>to maybe build it</i>

44:52.807 --> 44:55.891
<i>just a little bit better</i>
<i>than we did before.</i>

